data.text:
As of 2020, Rocklin has a population of 73,261. Major employers in Rocklin are concentrated in education, technology services, commercial, and retail. From 2015 to 2020, jobs in Rocklin increased from 27,853 to 31,290, an increase of 12.3%. This increase outpaces the national growth rate by 12.3%. The city's top three industries are

Education and Hospitals (Local Government)

Retail

Professional, Scientific and Technical Services
